## 2. Theme system — EXL Services light default

- **`<html>` MUST have `suppressHydrationWarning`** and the active `dark` class (or none) applied by `next-themes`. Do not hard-code `class="dark"`.
- **Default theme is `light`.** It is the brand-aligned EXL Services palette (orange `#FB4E0B` primary, deep blue secondary, warm-neutral grays). Dark is opt-in. Every component must look correct in **both** modes without a `dark:` override.
- **NEVER write `dark:*` Tailwind variants.** All color access goes through semantic tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, …). Tokens already invert via `:root` vs `.dark` in `aspire.svc/app/globals.css`.
- **NEVER add a parallel `.light` class.** Light is `:root` defaults, dark is `.dark`. There are exactly two modes.
- **No `prefers-color-scheme` media queries.** `next-themes` resolves user choice; do not bypass it.
- **Theme-toggle UI** belongs in `aspire.svc/components/layout/theme-toggle.tsx` (already exists, unmounted by default per `nextjs.mdc`). Mount it, do not invent a new toggle.
- All providers (theme, query, toaster, tooltip) live in `AppProviders` (`aspire.svc/components/providers/`). **Do not add a new top-level provider** without updating that file.

---

## 3. Color tokens — the only colors you may use

### 3.1 Allowed token classes

Use **only** these Tailwind utility roots, all of which resolve to CSS variables in `aspire.svc/app/globals.css`:

| Surface | Class |
|---|---|
| Page bg | `bg-background` |
| Body text | `text-foreground` |
| Muted surface | `bg-muted` |
| Muted text | `text-muted-foreground` |
| Card bg | `bg-card` |
| Card text | `text-card-foreground` |
| Popover/dropdown bg | `bg-popover` |
| Popover text | `text-popover-foreground` |
| Brand fill | `bg-primary` |
| On-brand text | `text-primary-foreground` |
| Brand text | `text-primary` |
| Subtle filled surface | `bg-secondary` / `text-secondary-foreground` |
| Hover/highlight surface | `bg-accent` / `text-accent-foreground` |
| Destructive fill | `bg-destructive` / `text-destructive` |
| Border | `border-border` |
| Input border | `border-input` |
| Focus ring | `ring-ring` (use with `ring-2`) |
| Sidebar surface | `bg-sidebar` / `text-sidebar-foreground` |
| Sidebar active | `bg-sidebar-accent` / `text-sidebar-accent-foreground` |
| Sidebar brand | `bg-sidebar-primary` / `text-sidebar-primary-foreground` |
| Sidebar border | `border-sidebar-border` |
| Chart series | `text-chart-1` … `text-chart-5` (or `var(--chart-1)` in `chartConfig`) |

### 3.2 Banned color usage

- **NEVER use raw hex values** (`#1677ff`, `#111827`, `#f3f4f6`, …) in `style={{}}`, `className`, `tailwind.config`, or `globals.css` outside of the token definitions.
- **NEVER use Tailwind palette classes** (`bg-gray-100`, `text-slate-700`, `border-zinc-200`, `text-red-500`, …) for theming. They do not invert with the active theme.
- **EXCEPTION — semantic accents only**: for status colors that have no semantic token (warning, success, info), use these alpha-blended pairs which read correctly in both modes:

  | Status | Bg | Border | Text |
  |---|---|---|---|
  | Warning | `bg-amber-500/10` | `border-amber-500/30` | `text-amber-600` (light) / `text-amber-400` (dark — use `dark:text-amber-400` here, this is the **only** allowed `dark:` variant) |
  | Success | `bg-emerald-500/10` | `border-emerald-500/30` | `text-emerald-600` / `dark:text-emerald-400` |
  | Info | `bg-sky-500/10` | `border-sky-500/30` | `text-sky-600` / `dark:text-sky-400` |
  | Destructive | `bg-destructive/10` | `border-destructive/30` | `text-destructive` |

  Prefer `text-destructive` (semantic) over `text-red-*` for errors.

- **NEVER use `oklch()`/`rgb()`/`hsl()` literals in components.** They belong only inside `aspire.svc/app/globals.css` token definitions.
- **NEVER define new top-level CSS variables in `globals.css`** without also exposing them through `@theme inline` and adding a row to the table above.

### 3.3 If `--primary` is currently grayscale (shadcn default)

The `PROJECT_NAME` seed `--primary` is near-black. If a brand color is needed, change it **once** in `aspire.svc/app/globals.css` for both `:root` and `.dark` (see `doc/web-stylng/08-arb-sherpa-mapping.md` §3 for OKLCH recipes). Do **not** hard-code brand hex per component.

