## 4. Typography

### 4.1 Font families

- **Sans (default everywhere)**: `font-sans` → `var(--font-geist-sans)`. **Inherits on `<body>`** — do not respecify in components.
- **Mono**: `font-mono` → `var(--font-geist-mono)`. Use for code, JSON, request IDs, keyboard chips, log values.
- **Heading**: `font-heading` is aliased to `--font-sans` — same as body. Do not introduce a new heading font without updating `globals.css`.
- **NEVER set `fontFamily` inline** (e.g. `style={{ fontFamily: "monospace" }}` or `style={{ fontFamily: '"-apple-system, …"' }}`). Use `font-sans` / `font-mono` classes only.

### 4.2 Type scale (use these utilities, in this order of preference)

| Use | Class |
|---|---|
| KPI metric | `text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight` |
| Page title (`h1`) | `text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight` |
| Section heading (`h2`) | `text-lg font-semibold` |
| Subsection (`h3`) | `text-base font-medium` |
| Body | `text-sm` (default) |
| Body strong | `text-sm font-medium text-foreground` |
| Body muted | `text-sm text-muted-foreground` |
| Label / small caption | `text-xs` |
| Tag / pill text | `text-xs font-medium` |
| Code body / JSON / request ID | `font-mono text-xs` (small) or `font-mono text-sm` (medium) |
| Section label uppercase | `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground` |

### 4.3 Line height

- **Body / chat assistant text**: `leading-relaxed` (1.625) for prose.
- **User chat bubble**: `leading-normal` (1.5).
- **Default elsewhere**: Tailwind defaults — do not override unless the design demands it.

### 4.4 Letter spacing

- **Tracking-tight (`tracking-tight`)** on metric numbers and large headings only.
- **Tracking-wider (`tracking-wider`)** on uppercase labels and short pills (e.g. `NEW`).
- **Do not** set custom `letterSpacing` inline.

### 4.5 Forbidden font-related patterns

- `style={{ fontSize: 13 }}` and similar inline numeric font sizes — use `text-*` classes.
- `style={{ fontWeight: 600 }}` — use `font-semibold` / `font-medium` / `font-bold`.
- Custom font imports beyond Geist Sans / Geist Mono.

---

## 5. Border radius

Use the tokenised radius scale defined in `aspire.svc/app/globals.css` (`--radius` = 0.625rem; `--radius-sm` … `--radius-4xl` derived).

| Element | Class |
|---|---|
| Tag / chip / `<kbd>` | `rounded-sm` (≈ 6 px) |
| Inputs, small buttons, tool blocks | `rounded-md` (≈ 8 px) |
| Cards, popovers, dropdowns | `rounded-lg` (≈ 10 px) |
| Modals, large surfaces, chat input bar | `rounded-xl` (≈ 14 px) |
| Hero pills, prominent CTAs | `rounded-2xl` (≈ 18 px) |
| Avatar / round controls (stop button, dot) | `rounded-full` |

- **NEVER use `rounded-[7px]`-style arbitrary values.** Round to the nearest scale step.
- **Sharp corners (`rounded-none`)** only for full-bleed dividers or table-internal borders.

---

## 6. Shadow

| Use | Class |
|---|---|
| Subtle elevation (cards on page) | `shadow-sm` |
| Inputs, chat input bar | `shadow-sm` |
| Dropdowns, popovers, dialogs | `shadow-md` |
| Floating overlays (toasts) | `shadow-lg` (Sonner default) |
| Focus halo on inputs | `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-0` |
| Brand focus halo on chat-style input | `focus-within:ring-2 focus-within:ring-primary/20` |

- **NEVER set `boxShadow:` inline** with a custom rgba.
- **NEVER stack two shadow utilities on the same element.**

