## 11. Per-component rules

> Every per-component file in `doc/web-stylng/06-components/` ends with the rules below extracted as do/don't. This section is the binding summary. Where a recipe is too long for inline, follow the link.

### 11.1 App header (top navbar) — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/01-navbar.md`

- **MUST**: 56-px tall (`h-14`), full width, sticky (`sticky top-0 z-10`), `bg-background`, `border-b border-border`. No padding tricks; just `px-4`.
- **MUST**: place sidebar collapse button on the left, brand logo right next to it. Account / theme controls on the right (`ml-auto` cluster).
- **MUST**: the `<button>` for the sidebar toggle uses `lucide-react` `PanelLeftClose` / `PanelLeftOpen` icons inside a `Button variant="ghost" size="icon"`.
- **SHOULD**: render a version pill via shadcn `<Badge variant="secondary" className="text-xs">v{version}</Badge>`. The pill must link to release notes (target `_blank` with `rel="noopener noreferrer"`). Pure decorative bouncing emojis are not required.
- **MUST NOT**: hardcode `#1677ff`, `bg-white`, `text-gray-*`. Use semantic tokens.
- **MUST NOT**: nest `<button>` inside `<button>` (per `nextjs.mdc`). Use `buttonVariants` for non-`<button>` triggers.

### 11.2 Sidebar — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/02-sidebar.md`

- **MUST** use shadcn `Sidebar` family from `aspire.svc/components/ui/`. Do not roll a custom sider.
- **MUST** drive widths from CSS variables `--sidebar-width` (220 or 260) and `--sidebar-width-icon` (80 or 56) — set in `globals.css`, do not override per page.
- **MUST** persist collapse state via `SidebarPreferences` + `AppConfig.sidebarStorageKey` (per `nextjs.mdc`). Do not invent new storage keys.
- **MUST** group menu items with shadcn `SidebarGroup` + `SidebarGroupLabel`. Group label class: `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground`.
- **MUST** resolve nav item icons in the **client** via `NavigationIconResolver` (icons are not serializable across the Server→Client boundary; `nextjs.mdc` rule).
- **MUST** use `bg-sidebar` / `text-sidebar-foreground` (not generic `bg-background`).
- **MUST** mark active item with `bg-sidebar-accent text-sidebar-accent-foreground`. Hover: `hover:bg-sidebar-accent/50`.
- **MUST** divide pinned bottom block (e.g. usage indicator, "Open Chat") with `border-t border-sidebar-border`.
- **NEW BADGE** alongside menu labels uses `<Badge variant="secondary" className="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider">NEW</Badge>`. Do not inline-style it.

### 11.3 Cards & metrics — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/03-cards-and-metrics.md`

- **MUST** use shadcn `Card` + `CardHeader` + `CardContent` + `CardTitle` + `CardDescription`. Default padding `p-6` is correct; do not override.
- **KPI label** = `text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground`.
- **KPI value** = `text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground`.
- **Compact KPI value** (two-up grid inside a card) = `text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground`.
- **Label-to-value spacing**: `mt-2`.
- **KPI grid**: `grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`. Do not use Tremor `<Grid>` / `<Col>`.
- **Filter strip above charts**: `grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3` (or appropriate). Use `gap-4` for filters, `gap-6` for KPIs.
- **NEVER** use `text-tremor-content`, `text-tremor-content-strong`, etc. Tremor classes are forbidden.

### 11.4 Tables — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/04-tables.md`

- **MUST** use shadcn `Table*` family + `@tanstack/react-table` for logic.
- **Wrapper**: `<div className="rounded-lg border border-border overflow-x-auto">`.
- **Density default**: `[&_td]:py-2 [&_th]:py-2`. For dense log-style tables: `[&_td]:py-1 [&_th]:py-1` and `h-8` rows.
- **Cell truncation**: `overflow-hidden text-ellipsis whitespace-nowrap` on cells holding identifiers or paths.
- **Hover**: `hover:bg-muted/50` on `<TableRow>` whenever the row is clickable.
- **Sortable header**: `<Button variant="ghost" size="sm">` containing label + `<ArrowUpDown className="ml-2 size-3" />` (or `<ArrowUp />` / `<ArrowDown />` when sorted).
- **Empty state**: `<TableCell colSpan={…} className="h-24 text-center text-muted-foreground">No results.</TableCell>`.
- **Loading state**: shadcn `Skeleton` rows OR `<Loader2 className="mx-auto size-4 animate-spin" />` in a single full-span row.
- **Row identity**: pass `getRowId: (row) => row.id ?? String(index)` so expansion/selection survives re-fetches.
- **Sub-rows**: render as real `<TableRow>` siblings (preferred) or as a single full-`colSpan` cell. Match the LiteLLM `renderChildRows` / `renderSubComponent` split — never both for the same table.

### 11.5 Buttons — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/05-buttons.md`

- **MUST** use shadcn `<Button>` for every clickable affordance. The variant grid:

  | Need | Variant |
  |---|---|
  | Primary CTA | `variant="default"` |
  | Secondary | `variant="outline"` |
  | Tertiary / icon-only | `variant="ghost"` |
  | Inline link | `variant="link"` |
  | Destructive | `variant="destructive"` |

- **Sizes**: `default`, `sm`, `lg`, `icon`. **Always pass an explicit size for icon-only buttons**: `size="icon"`.
- **Loading state** is `disabled={true}` plus `<Loader2 className="mr-2 size-4 animate-spin" />` before the label. Do not change the label text to "Loading…".
- **Disabled state** must come from props, not from inline color overrides. shadcn `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed` is sufficient.
- **Three-state Send/Stop pattern (chat)**:
  - Idle (no text): `<Button disabled>` with `<Send className="size-4" />`.
  - Ready: `<Button>` with `<Send className="size-4" />`.
  - Streaming: `<Button variant="outline" size="icon" className="rounded-full">` with `<Square className="size-3" />`.
- **NEVER inline-style** `background`, `color`, `border`, `borderRadius`, `padding` on buttons. If the design needs something not in shadcn variants, add a new `cva` variant in the same file.
- **NEW pill** inside a button: `<Badge variant="secondary" className="ml-2 text-[9px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-1.5">NEW</Badge>`. Never roll a custom `<span>`.

### 11.6 Tags & badges — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/06-tags-and-badges.md`

- **MUST** use shadcn `Badge` for status pills, version pills, count chips.
- **Variants**:
  - `variant="default"` for brand / primary count.
  - `variant="secondary"` for neutral / version / count.
  - `variant="outline"` for outlined chips (rare).
  - `variant="destructive"` for error.
  - **Status colors** beyond destructive: use the alpha-blended pairs from §3.2.
- **Status semantics**:

  | Status | Class |
  |---|---|
  | Success | `bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/30` |
  | Warning | `bg-amber-500/10 text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 border-amber-500/30` |
  | Info / Processing | `bg-sky-500/10 text-sky-600 dark:text-sky-400 border-sky-500/30` |
  | Destructive | `bg-destructive/10 text-destructive border-destructive/30` |
  | Purple (policy) | `bg-violet-500/10 text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400 border-violet-500/30` |

- **Keyboard chip (`<kbd>`)**: see §11.16 — never a custom `<span>`.
- **Function-name chip on tool blocks**: `absolute -top-2 left-3 bg-background text-muted-foreground border border-border rounded-sm px-1.5 text-[10px] font-mono`. Position the parent `relative`.

### 11.7 Forms & inputs — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/07-forms-and-inputs.md`

- **MUST** use shadcn `Form` + `react-hook-form` + `zod` for any form with more than one field.
- **MUST** wrap each control in `<FormField>` → `<FormItem>` → `<FormLabel>` → `<FormControl>` → `<FormDescription>` → `<FormMessage>`.
- **Input height**: shadcn default. Do not override.
- **Required marker**: rely on `<FormMessage>` + zod schema, not a manual red asterisk.
- **Multi-line text**: shadcn `Textarea`. **NEVER** roll a bare `<textarea>` outside of `chat` (see §11.14).
- **Single-select with search**: shadcn `Combobox`. Plain `Select` only when the option list is < 10 fixed items.
- **Multi-select**: shadcn registry `MultiSelect` (or Combobox in multi mode). Never `<select multiple>`.
- **Switch**: shadcn `Switch`. Always pair with a `<Label>`.
- **Radio**: shadcn `RadioGroup` + `RadioGroupItem`. For card-style radios see §11.15.
- **File upload**: `react-dropzone` styled with shadcn primitives. No custom drag handlers.
- **Numeric**: shadcn `Input type="number"` with `min` / `max` / `step` attributes.
- **Date range**: shadcn `Calendar` inside a `Popover` (shadcn `DateRangePicker` recipe).
- **Help icon next to label**: `<Tooltip><TooltipTrigger asChild><HelpCircle className="ml-1 size-4 text-muted-foreground cursor-help" /></TooltipTrigger><TooltipContent side="top" className="max-w-xs">…</TooltipContent></Tooltip>`. Never roll a custom tooltip atom.
- **Submit button**: `<Button type="submit" disabled={form.formState.isSubmitting}>{form.formState.isSubmitting ? <Loader2 className="mr-2 size-4 animate-spin" /> : null}Save</Button>`.
- **Form-item gap**: `space-y-4` between items (16 px), `space-y-6` between sections.

### 11.8 Modals (Dialog) — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/08-modals.md`

- **MUST** use shadcn `Dialog`. Banned: `antd Modal`, `<dialog>` element directly.
- **Sizing**:
  - Confirm: `<DialogContent className="sm:max-w-md">` (≈ 28 rem).
  - Single-form: `sm:max-w-lg`.
  - Multi-section: `sm:max-w-2xl` or `sm:max-w-3xl`.
  - Full-bleed: `sm:max-w-[90vw]`.
- **Header**: `<DialogHeader>` containing `<DialogTitle>` + `<DialogDescription>`. Title may include a leading lucide icon for tone (`AlertCircle` for destructive).
- **Body wrapper**: `<div className="space-y-4">` for stacked sections.
- **Footer**: `<DialogFooter>` with **`<Button variant="outline">Cancel</Button>` first, primary action second**. Reverse the visual order with `flex-row-reverse` if needed — this is the keyboard tab order.
- **Destructive confirmation pattern (typed-to-confirm)**:
  1. Wrap resource summary in a tinted `<Card className="bg-destructive/5 border-destructive/30">` with header `bg-destructive/10`.
  2. Show key/value pairs as `<dl className="space-y-2 text-sm">` with `<dt className="font-semibold">` / `<dd>`.
  3. Below, `<Label>Type <code className="font-mono">{name}</code> to confirm</Label>` then a shadcn `<Input autoFocus value={typed} onChange={…}>`.
  4. Disable the destructive button: `disabled={typed !== name || loading}`.
  5. Show `<Loader2 className="mr-2 size-4 animate-spin" />` when `loading`.
- **NEVER** use `theme.useToken()`. Use the alpha-blended status colors from §3.2.

### 11.9 Drawers (Sheet) — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/09-drawer-log-details.md`

- **MUST** use shadcn `Sheet` (Radix Dialog with `side="right"`). Banned: `antd Drawer`.
- **Width**: `<SheetContent className="w-[60%] sm:max-w-none">` for log-detail style; `w-[400px] sm:max-w-md` for a narrow side sheet.
- **Custom sticky header pattern** (when default `SheetHeader` isn't enough — e.g. log details with J/K/ESC nav):
  ```tsx
  <SheetContent className="w-[60%] sm:max-w-none p-0">
    <div className="sticky top-0 z-10 bg-background border-b border-border px-6 py-4 space-y-2">
      {/* row 0: provider logo + model name */}
      {/* row 1: request id (left) + nav cluster (right) */}
      {/* row 2: status tag + env tag + timestamps */}
    </div>
    <div className="p-6">
      <Tabs defaultValue="request">…</Tabs>
    </div>
  </SheetContent>
  ```
- **Padding constants**:
  - Header: `px-6 py-4`.
  - Content: `p-6`.
  - Section gap: `space-y-3` to `space-y-4`.
- **Keyboard nav (J/K/ESC)** must be wired with a `useEffect` that adds a `keydown` listener on `window` and removes it on cleanup. Use the same pattern as LiteLLM (`doc/web-stylng/06-components/09-drawer-log-details.md` §12). The chips use the `<Kbd>` component (§11.16).
- **Request ID** rendered as `<button>` with shadcn `<Button variant="ghost">` containing a `<Copy />` lucide icon. On click: `navigator.clipboard.writeText(...)` with the non-secure-context fallback (`doc/web-stylng/06-components/13-code-and-json.md` §7), then `toast.success("Copied")`.
- **Timestamps**: `date-fns` `format(date, "MMM d, yyyy h:mm:ss a")` and `formatDistanceToNow(date)`. **Never `moment`.**
- **Drawer max-height for embedded JSON**: 400 px → `max-h-[400px] overflow-auto`. For metadata blocks: 300 px → `max-h-[300px] overflow-auto`.

### 11.10 Notifications (Sonner) — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/10-notifications.md`

- **MUST** use `sonner`. Mount **once** in `AppProviders` as `<Toaster position="top-right" richColors />`. Banned: `antd notification`.
- **API**: `toast.success("Title", { description: "…" })`, `toast.error`, `toast.warning`, `toast.info`. Use a thin wrapper at `aspire.svc/lib/notifications.ts`.
- **`Notifications.fromBackend(err)` is mandatory** for API errors. Port the LiteLLM 14-category classifier verbatim from `src/components/molecules/notifications_manager.tsx`. The classifier owns: title selection, severity mapping (auth/forbidden/rate-limit/budget/server/etc. → `error`/`warning`/`info`), and duration (3.5 / 4 / 5 / 6 / 7 / 8 s).
- **Durations** (default by variant — Sonner's `duration` in ms):
  - success: `3500`
  - info: `4000`
  - warning: `5000`
  - error: `6000`
  - server error / rate limit / budget: `7000`–`8000`
- **Position**: `top-right`. Do not change per call.
- **Show progress / pause on hover**: enable globally on `<Toaster richColors closeButton />`.
- **NEVER** call `toast(...)` inline in a component for an API error — always go through `Notifications.fromBackend(err)`.

### 11.11 Tooltips & popovers — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/11-tooltips-and-popovers.md`

- **Tooltip**: shadcn `<Tooltip>` only. Wrap with `<TooltipTrigger asChild>` to forward to a real control. `<TooltipProvider>` is already mounted in `AppProviders`.
- **Popover**: shadcn `<Popover>` for click-triggered rich content (filters, MCP picker, column settings).
- **NEVER** roll a custom positioned `<div className="absolute …">` with `getBoundingClientRect` math. Radix Popper handles flip/shift.
- **Help-icon tooltip pattern** (replaces LiteLLM's custom `Tooltip` atom):

  ```tsx
  <Tooltip>
    <TooltipTrigger asChild>
      <HelpCircle className="ml-1 size-4 text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground cursor-help" />
    </TooltipTrigger>
    <TooltipContent side="top" className="max-w-xs">{content}</TooltipContent>
  </Tooltip>
  ```
- **Tooltip side**: `top` default; `right` for sidebar collapsed-mode item labels; `bottom` only when no space above.

### 11.12 Charts — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/12-charts.md`

- **MUST** use shadcn `Chart*` (Recharts) family. Banned: `@tremor/react` charts.
- **Series colors come from `--chart-1` … `--chart-5`**. Define them in `aspire.svc/app/globals.css` (both `:root` and `.dark`). Suggested OKLCH values are in `doc/web-stylng/08-arb-sherpa-mapping.md` §5 — sky / teal / indigo / amber / rose. Use these.
- **`chartConfig`** maps logical series keys to color references:

  ```tsx
  const chartConfig = {
    apiRequests: { label: "API Requests", color: "var(--chart-1)" },
    cacheHits:   { label: "Cache Hits",   color: "var(--chart-2)" },
  } satisfies ChartConfig;
  ```

- **Tooltip**: `<ChartTooltip cursor={false} content={<ChartTooltipContent />} />`. Do not write a custom tooltip unless data shape forces it.
- **Legend**: `<ChartLegend content={<ChartLegendContent />} />`.
- **Series dot in custom tooltip** (if needed): `<span className="size-2 shrink-0 rounded-full ring-2 ring-background" style={{ backgroundColor: "var(--chart-N)" }} />` — the `style` here is permitted because the color comes from a theme variable.
- **NEVER** pass color names like `"sky"` / `"teal"` / `"indigo"` directly to charts — pass `var(--chart-N)`.
- **Y-axis width** for currency / large numbers: `width={48}`. For percentages: `width={32}`.
- **Number formatters** live in `aspire.svc/lib/format.ts` (create if absent). Reuse — do not redefine in components.

### 11.13 Code & JSON — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/13-code-and-json.md`

- **Inline `<pre>`** for ad-hoc JSON: `<pre className="rounded-md bg-muted p-3 text-xs text-foreground font-mono whitespace-pre-wrap break-words">`. No inline `style`.
- **Syntax-highlighted code blocks**:
  - Library: `react-syntax-highlighter` (Prism).
  - **Style**: `oneDark` (import from `react-syntax-highlighter/dist/esm/styles/prism`). `coy` is forbidden (light-only).
  - Wrap with `<SyntaxHighlighter language={lang} style={oneDark} PreTag="div" wrapLongLines>`.
- **Markdown**: `react-markdown` + `remark-gfm`. Pass a `code` renderer that routes fenced blocks to `SyntaxHighlighter` and inline code to `<code className="rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">`.
- **JSON tree**: `react-json-view-lite` with `darkStyles` (not `defaultStyles`). Wrapper: `<div className="rounded-md bg-muted/40 p-3 max-h-[400px] overflow-auto">`. Force tree contrast via `<div className="[&_[role='tree']]:bg-card [&_[role='tree']]:text-card-foreground">`.
- **Side-by-side request/response**: `<div className="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4">` with two shadcn `<Card>` blocks each containing `<CardHeader>` + a copy `<Button variant="ghost" size="icon"><Copy className="size-4" /></Button>` + a `<CardContent className="overflow-auto max-h-96">`.
- **Copy** uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(...)` with a non-secure-context fallback (`document.execCommand("copy")`). Put the helper in `aspire.svc/lib/clipboard.ts`. Always toast result through `Notifications.success("Copied")` / `Notifications.fromBackend(err)`.

### 11.14 Chat surface — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/14-chat.md`

> Chat is the largest porting cost. Every hex must be replaced with a token.

- **Outer shell**: `<div className="flex h-screen w-screen overflow-hidden bg-background font-sans">`. **Do not** override `fontFamily` to a system stack.
- **Left sidebar** (chat-specific): `<div className="flex flex-col bg-sidebar border-r border-sidebar-border transition-[width] duration-200 ease-[cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1)]" style={{ width: collapsed ? 56 : 260 }}>` — width via CSS variable is preferred (`--chat-sidebar-width`).
- **Sidebar nav item**: `<Button variant="ghost" className={cn("justify-start gap-2.5 h-9 w-full", isActive && "bg-sidebar-accent text-sidebar-accent-foreground")}>`. Hover: handled by `variant="ghost"` defaults.
- **User message bubble**: `<div className="bg-muted text-foreground rounded-2xl px-3.5 py-2.5 text-sm leading-normal max-w-[72%] whitespace-pre-wrap break-words">`. Right-align via parent `flex justify-end`.
- **Assistant message body** (no bubble): `<div className="text-sm text-foreground leading-relaxed max-w-[80%] prose prose-sm dark:prose-invert">` with `<ReactMarkdown remarkPlugins={[remarkGfm]} components={{ code: MarkdownCodeRenderer }}>`. Left-align.
- **Edit mode for user message**: surround with `<div className="bg-background border border-input rounded-xl overflow-hidden focus-within:ring-2 focus-within:ring-primary/20">` then a `<Textarea className="border-0 focus-visible:ring-0 resize-none">` plus a footer row `border-t border-border` with shadcn `<Button variant="outline" size="sm">Cancel</Button>` and `<Button size="sm">Save & Send</Button>`.
- **Input bar**: `<div className="bg-background border border-input rounded-xl shadow-sm overflow-hidden focus-within:ring-2 focus-within:ring-primary/20">` containing a `<Textarea>` + a footer row with `border-t border-border`.
- **Send button** (three states) — see §11.5.
- **MCP picker button**: `<Button variant="outline" size="sm" className="gap-1"><Plus className="size-4" />{count > 0 && <span className="text-xs text-primary font-medium">{count}</span>}</Button>` inside a shadcn `<Popover>`.
- **Tool-call block**: shadcn `<Collapsible>` containing the function-name chip pattern from §11.6 and a `<pre>` body styled per §11.13. Section labels above each section: `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground mb-1`.
- **Typing indicator**: a small 3-dot pulse component using `tw-animate-css`. Centralise in `components/chat/typing-dots.tsx`.
- **Hover edit / hover copy** buttons: `<Button variant="ghost" size="icon" className="size-7 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100">`. Wrap parent with `group`.

### 11.15 Mode picker (card-style radio) — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/15-mode-picker.md`

- **MUST** be a real radio (accessible). Pattern:

  ```tsx
  <RadioGroup value={value} onValueChange={onChange} className="flex gap-4">
    {options.map((opt) => {
      const selected = value === opt.value;
      const Icon = opt.icon;
      return (
        <Label key={opt.value} htmlFor={opt.value} className={cn(
          "flex-1 cursor-pointer rounded-xl border-2 p-6 transition-all",
          selected ? "border-primary bg-primary/10" : "border-border bg-background hover:bg-accent/50",
        )}>
          <RadioGroupItem id={opt.value} value={opt.value} className="sr-only" />
          <div className={cn(
            "mb-4 flex size-10 items-center justify-center rounded-[10px]",
            selected ? "bg-primary/15 text-primary" : "bg-muted text-muted-foreground",
          )}>
            <Icon className="size-5" />
          </div>
          <div className="text-base font-semibold text-foreground">{opt.title}</div>
          <div className="mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground">{opt.description}</div>
        </Label>
      );
    })}
  </RadioGroup>
  ```

- **Banned**: `<div onClick>` cards (not keyboard-accessible).
- **Banned**: hex colors (`#4f46e5`, `#eef2ff`, `#e0e7ff`). Use `border-primary` / `bg-primary/10` / `bg-primary/15`.

### 11.16 Keyboard chips — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/16-keyboard-shortcut-chips.md`

- **MUST** use a shared `<Kbd>` component at `aspire.svc/components/ui/kbd.tsx`:

  ```tsx
  export function Kbd({ children, className }: { children: React.ReactNode; className?: string }) {
    return (
      <kbd className={cn(
        "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded border border-border bg-muted",
        "px-1.5 py-0 font-mono text-xs text-muted-foreground ml-1",
        className,
      )}>
        {children}
      </kbd>
    );
  }
  ```

- Use for J / K / ESC navigation, command-palette `⌘K` hints, sidebar quick-find labels.
- **NEVER** roll a `<span>` with inline `border` / `borderRadius` / `padding` / `background` for shortcut chips.

### 11.17 Themed cards (semantic surfaces) — `doc/web-stylng/06-components/17-themed-cards-error.md`

- **Use a `ThemedCard` component** at `aspire.svc/components/ui/themed-card.tsx` with variants `destructive | warning | success | info`. Recipe in `doc/web-stylng/06-components/17-themed-cards-error.md` §6.
- **NEVER** use `theme.useToken()`. Antd is banned.
- **NEVER** hard-code red/amber/sky/emerald hex.
- **For inline single-line notices**: shadcn `Alert` (`variant="default" | "destructive"`). For warning/info, use the alpha-blended classes from §3.2 inside `<Alert>` until shadcn adds those variants natively.

