## 12. Provider logos & images

- Brand / provider logos (OpenAI, Anthropic, …) are **not icons**. Store under `public/providers/<key>.svg` and load via `next/image`:
  ```tsx
  <Image src={`/providers/${key}.svg`} alt={displayName} width={24} height={24} className="shrink-0" />
  ```
- **Sizes**: `24` in drawer headers; `18` in table cells; `14` inline next to text.
- **`object-contain`** for logos with non-square art.
- **Runtime branding override** (LiteLLM-style logo / favicon swap) — if needed, read from a server endpoint and store in a `BrandingService` (`aspire.svc/lib/`) per `nextjs.mdc`'s `aspire.svc/lib/` rule. **Do not** mutate `<head>` from a leaf component.

---

## 13. Loading, empty, and error states

Every list, table, card, panel, page **MUST** handle three states explicitly.

### 13.1 Loading

- **Inline / button**: `<Loader2 className="size-4 animate-spin" />`.
- **Block / row**: shadcn `<Skeleton className="h-N w-full" />` repeated 3–5 times.
- **Page-level (between Suspense boundaries)**: a centred `<Loader2 className="size-6 animate-spin text-muted-foreground" />`.
- **Optimistic UI**: prefer `useOptimistic` (React 19) over a spinner when the action is fast and reversible.

### 13.2 Empty

- Centered text: `<p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">No results.</p>` inside a min-height container (`min-h-32`).
- Page-level empty: shadcn community `<EmptyState>` if available, otherwise a `<Card>` with icon + title + description + primary action.

### 13.3 Error

- API errors → `Notifications.fromBackend(err)` (toast).
- Form errors → `<FormMessage>` rendered by shadcn `Form`.
- Page-level fatal → `aspire.svc/app/error.tsx` / `aspire.svc/app/global-error.tsx` (per `nextjs.mdc`).

---

## 14. Accessibility (mandatory)

- Every interactive control **MUST** be a real `<button>`, `<a href>`, or `<input>` — never `<div onClick>`. Card-style radios use `<Label>` + `<RadioGroupItem className="sr-only">` (§11.15).
- Every `<Button size="icon">` **MUST** have either visible text inside or an `aria-label`.
- Every `<Label>` **MUST** be tied to a control via `htmlFor` (or implicit nesting).
- Every `<img>` **MUST** have `alt` (decorative: `alt=""`).
- Every interactive list **MUST** support keyboard navigation. Tables with row clicks: rows are `<tr>` (not focusable) — render row-level interactivity via a `<Button variant="ghost">` cell or via a checkbox column.
- Focus states: rely on shadcn's `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring` defaults. **Do not** disable focus rings.
- Color contrast: text on `bg-background` already meets WCAG AA via OKLCH lightness gap. Custom semantic colors (amber/sky/emerald) **must** be checked for AA when used as text.
- Modals (`Dialog`) and drawers (`Sheet`) trap focus by default (Radix). Do not bypass with `restoreFocus={false}` style props.
- Tooltips **must not** be the only carrier of essential information.

---

## 15. Theme-driven layout & responsive design

Layout for **pages** and **components** must read as one coherent system: modern, fluid across devices, and anchored in the **theme** (semantic tokens + shared variables in `aspire.svc/app/globals.css`), not one-off styling.

### 15.1 Theme-first layout (mandatory)

- **Surfaces, type, borders, radius, shadows, and spacing** for layout shells (page background, cards, headers, sidebars, main scroll regions) **MUST** use semantic Tailwind token classes and the documented CSS variables (see §2–§7, especially §7.2 for shell dimensions). Prefer tokens over raw values so light/dark and future token tweaks stay consistent.
- **Do not** hard-code layout colors or theme-adjacent values (`bg-white`, `#…`, arbitrary `h-[413px]` for chrome) when a token or shared variable exists. If a new layout token is truly needed, add it **once** in `aspire.svc/app/globals.css` + `@theme inline` (per §3.2) rather than scattering literals in components.
- **Fluid width**: constrain content with `max-w-*`, `min-w-0`, and flex/grid `fr` units so layouts **adapt** to viewport width; reserve fixed widths for small controls and documented patterns (e.g. icon buttons, drawer recipes in §11.9).

### 15.2 Modern layouts on every screen class

- **Target devices**: phone (small touch), **tablet**, **laptop**, and **large desktop** (home / workstation monitors). Every screen must remain **usable**: readable type, adequate tap targets (≥ ~44 px where primary actions are touch), no accidental overflow except **intentional** horizontal scroll (e.g. data tables).
- **Modern bar**: prefer clear hierarchy, consistent spacing scale (§7), responsive grids/flex, and shadcn primitives that already encode accessible patterns — avoid cramped fixed multi-column desktop-only layouts that break on narrow viewports.
- **Dynamic behavior**: navigation chrome (sidebar, sheets, dialogs) should **respond** to viewport (collapse, full-width modals on small screens, scrollable regions with `min-h-0` in flex parents) rather than assuming a single desktop width.

### 15.3 Breakpoints & Tailwind patterns

- **Mobile-first**: write base classes for the smallest viewport, then scale up with `sm:` (640), `md:` (768), `lg:` (1024), `xl:` (1280), `2xl:` (1536).
- **KPI grid**: `grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6`. Always.
- **Sidebar**: collapse on `<lg` automatically (shadcn `Sidebar` does this).
- **Modals**: max-width caps with `sm:max-w-*`. Full-screen on mobile is the shadcn default for narrower phones.
- **Drawers**: side sheet becomes bottom sheet on `<sm` when appropriate (use `<Sheet side="right" className="w-[60%] sm:max-w-none data-[state=open]:slide-in-from-bottom sm:data-[state=open]:slide-in-from-right">` or split components).
- **Tables**: wrap in `overflow-x-auto`. Do not hide columns silently — use a column-visibility menu.
- **Never** use fixed pixel widths for primary content surfaces. Use `max-w-*` and let the parent constrain.

---

## 16. Server vs client styling concerns

- **Icons are not serializable.** Server components must pass icon **string ids**; client code resolves them via `NavigationIconResolver` or equivalent (`nextjs.mdc` rule).
- **CVA variants** can be evaluated in server components. **`useTheme()`** cannot. If a component needs theme-aware values at render time (rare), mark it `"use client"`.
- **Class strings produced by `cn()` are pure** — fine in either environment.
- **Do not** import `sonner` from a server component. Toasts are client-side; throw or return an error and let a client boundary toast it.

---

## 17. File and directory rules (UI-specific)

- New shadcn primitives: `npx shadcn@latest add <name>` → land in `aspire.svc/components/ui/<name>.tsx`. **Never edit a primitive directly** unless adding a variant via `cva`; prefer wrapping it in `components/<feature>/`.
- New non-shadcn UI components (layout chrome, feature-specific blocks): `components/<feature>/<KebabCase>.tsx`.
- Page UI: `aspire.svc/components/pages/<route-segment>/...` per `nextjs.mdc`. Route `page.tsx` files are **containers only**.
- Icons (only when truly missing from Lucide): `components/icons/<Name>.tsx` as a typed React component.
- Theming: edit `aspire.svc/app/globals.css` only.
- Hooks: `hooks/use-*.ts(x)`. Component-local hooks may live next to the component.
- Variant tables (`cva`): co-locate with the component file or extract to `components/<feature>/<name>.variants.ts` if reused.

---

## 18. Pre-merge checklist for any UI change

A change is **not** ready to merge until **every** box is checked.

1. [ ] No `dark:*` Tailwind variant added (except the documented status-text exception in §3.2).
2. [ ] No raw hex value in any `style` prop, `className`, or `globals.css` outside token definitions.
3. [ ] No Tailwind palette class (`bg-gray-*`, `text-slate-*`, etc.) used for theming.
4. [ ] No `style={{ fontFamily: … }}`, `style={{ fontSize: N }}`, `style={{ fontWeight: N }}`.
5. [ ] No banned dependency imported (`antd`, `@tremor/react`, `@heroicons/react`, `@remixicon/react`, `moment`).
6. [ ] All icons from `lucide-react`, sized with `size-N`, colored with token classes.
7. [ ] Class composition uses `cn()`; variants use `cva()`.
8. [ ] All clickable affordances are `<Button>` (or `buttonVariants` on a real control).
9. [ ] Loading state uses `<Loader2 className="animate-spin" />` or shadcn `Skeleton`.
10. [ ] Empty state explicit.
11. [ ] Error state goes through `Notifications.fromBackend(err)` for API errors, `<FormMessage>` for form errors.
12. [ ] Tooltip / popover via shadcn (no custom positioning math).
13. [ ] Modal via shadcn `Dialog`; drawer via shadcn `Sheet`.
14. [ ] Tables use shadcn `Table*` + `@tanstack/react-table` with explicit `getRowId`.
15. [ ] Charts read colors from `var(--chart-N)` via `chartConfig`.
16. [ ] Code blocks use `oneDark` Prism style; JSON viewer uses `darkStyles`.
17. [ ] Date formatting uses `date-fns` or `dayjs` (not `moment`).
18. [ ] Every interactive control is keyboard-navigable; icon-only buttons have `aria-label`.
19. [ ] Layout uses CSS variables for sidebar widths and header height — not per-component overrides.
20. [ ] Page/component layout uses theme tokens and shared variables where possible; no ad hoc theme-adjacent hex or one-off chrome dimensions.
21. [ ] Layout verified (or clearly constrained) for phone, tablet, laptop, and large desktop — fluid width, no unintended horizontal bleed.
22. [ ] Page route files are containers only; UI lives in `aspire.svc/components/pages/<segment>/`.
23. [ ] Any new exported props/types have TSDoc (`nextjs.mdc` rule).
24. [ ] Component looks correct in **both** `:root` (light) and `.dark` modes — verified by toggling, not assumed.

If any box is unchecked, the change is incomplete.

